1 A BILL for an Act to create and enact a new section to chapter 54-07 of the North Dakota
2 Century Code, relating to the children's cabinet and designated working groups; to repeal
3 section 50-06-43.1 of the North Dakota Century Code, relating to the children's cabinet; to
4 provide for a legislative management report; and to provide an appropriation.
5 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATIVE ASSEMBLY OF NORTH DAKOTA:
6 SECTION 1. A new section to chapter 54-07 of the North Dakota Century Code is created
7 and enacted as follows:
8 Children's cabinet - Membership - Duties - Working groups - Report.
9 1. The children's cabinet is created to assess, guide, and coordinate the care for children
10 and families across the state's branches of government and the tribal nations.
11 2. The children's cabinet is composed of:
12 a. The governor, or the governor's designee;
13 b. The chief justice of the supreme court, or the chief justice's designee;
14 c. A member of the house of representatives from an even-numbered legislative
15 district and a member of the house of representatives from an odd - numbered
16 legislative district appointed by the majority leader of the house of
17 representatives to serve two-year terms;
18 d. A member of the senate from an even-numbered legislative district and a
19 member of the senate from an odd - numbered legislative district appointed by the
20 majority leader of the senate to serve two-year terms;
21 e. The superintendent of public instruction, or the superintendent's designee;
22 f. The director of the committee on protection and advocacy, or the director's
23 designee;
