1 g. The commissioner of the department of health and human services, or the
2 commissioner's designee;
3 h. A representative of the tribal nations in the state, who is appointed by the
4 governor; and
5 i. Four individuals representing parents, private service providers, or other
6 community interests, who are appointed by the governor to serve a term of two
7 years, at the pleasure of the governor, and who are entitled to reimbursement
8 from the governor's office for travel and lodging at the same rate as provided for
9 state officers and employees.
10 3. The governor, in collaboration with the chairman of the legislative management, shall
11 appoint as the presiding officer of the children's cabinet a member of the governor's
12 cabinet or a legislator serving on the children's cabinet. The children's cabinet shall
13 select one of its members to serve as the vice-presiding officer.
14 4. The children's cabinet shall meet at least quarterly. Additional meetings may be held at
15 the discretion of the presiding officer.
16 5. The children's cabinet shall:
17 a. Coordinate broad-based leadership across programs, agencies, branches of
18 government, and tribal nations to meet the needs of children and families;
19 b. Develop strategies to address gaps or needs regarding early care and education,
20 medical and behavioral health, community, child welfare, and juvenile justice;
21 c. Develop strategies to provide for the full continuum of care in the delivery of
22 services, including promotion, prevention, early identification and intervention,
23 service delivery, and recovery;
24 d. Seek to engage cooperation across public and private service providers;
25 e. Provide a comprehensive vision for how and where children are best served,
26 attending to children and families in a respectful and relevant manner;
27 f. Seek strategies to provide services to children without consideration of prior
28 engagement with juvenile services;
29 g. Provide for the active participation of consumers and providers statewide on
30 advisory committees;
